title: Freshmen
description: Freshmen are students who have never attended college. Even if you have taken college courses during high school, you are still considered a freshman.

title: Transfer
description: Transfer students are students who have previously studied at other post-secondary institutions. Admission to York College is based on the strength of your post-secondary record(s). Your high school/secondary school record will be considered if you have completed fewer than 30 college credits.

title: Graduate Programs
description: York College is an excellent choice for graduate students who desire a quality educational experience at an affordable cost and offers opportunities for students at all stages of their careers. As a senior college of the City University of New York (CUNY), York College offers graduate degrees in Aviation Management (MS), Clinical Trial Management (MS), Physician Assistant (MS), Pharmaceutical Science and Business (MS), Social Work (MSW), and  Nursing Education (MS).

title: International Students
description: York College offers a unique blend of academic excellence and real-world experience, with over 60 major areas of study. At York College, you will acquire the intellectual, creative, and social tools you need to achieve life-long success while making a difference in our world.

title: Campus Tours
description: Take a guided tour of the York College campus and get a look at the Cardinal Nest! Be sure to have your confirmation email handy for the day of!

title: Reconnect
description: CUNY Reconnect is a new outreach initiative that helps re-enroll New Yorkers who earned some college credits but left school before finishing their degree.
